cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) because it deals with the credibility and representativeness of online reviews, which is a topic related to the social impact of technology. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it analyzes the social influence and selection biases that affect the submission of web reviews. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it involves the analysis of data from online retailers to understand the behavior of reviewers. It could also be categorized under cs.SD (Software Engineering) because it suggests ways to mitigate biases in online reviews, which is relevant to the design and development of software systems. Finally, it could be classified under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) because it deals with the interaction between users and online review systems, and how to improve the user experience.
